							<div class="serve on">
								<h2 class="pt0">Education</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Symphony Little Library</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve01.jpg" alt="Symphony Little Library">
									<p><strong>365 days 365 books 36.5℃, Share temperature of love from HDC daily.</strong><br />‘Building Symphony Little Library’ is a social contribution activity of donating talents and books, following talent-oriented philosophy of the late honorary president Mr. Chung Se Young. Through voluntary contribution of books and talents, Onnuri Study room, located in Jangjae-dong, Gunsan-si, opened first ‘Symphony Little Library’ by replacing outworn facilities and stocking 1,000 books.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="serve">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Education</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>ICAMP</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve02.jpg" alt="ICAMP">
									<p><strong>“Moving ICAMP” with reading instructors and social workers</strong><br />‘Moving ICAMP’ is Korea’s first mobile library with field study facilities donated by IPARK Corporate Citizenship. The ‘Moving ICAMP’ is converted from RV and is fully capable of handling bed and foods in ONE-STOP. The ‘Moving ICAMP’ aims to raise academic motivation and sense of independence for children from low-income households, by offering activities seen from school and books.</p>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="serve">
								<h2>Community</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Ondol Welfare Project</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve03.jpg" alt="Ondol Welfare Project">
									<p><strong>Ondol Welfare Project, Warmer Winter for the Community</strong><br />The project is led by Seoul city since November 2011, which aims to share hope and support to the suffering neighbors in our community. To help our neighbors, Hyundai Development Company delivered rice and winter clothes to 300 low-income households around Dongja-dong, Yongsan-gu.</p>
								</div>
							</div>			

							<div class="serve">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Community</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Blood Donation of Love Campaign</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve04.jpg" alt="Blood Donation of Love Campaign">
									<p><strong>Let’s donate our blood.</strong><br />Hyundai Development Company concluded blood donation agreement with Ministry of Health and Welfare and Korea National Red Cross, and 600 executives and staffs of Head office have started ‘Blood donation of love campaign.’ Our campaign will continue with our affiliated company and every work places by registering to blood donation membership.</p>
								</div>
							</div>			
							
							<div class="serve">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Community</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Relay Coal Briquette Delivery Campaign</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve05.jpg" alt="Relay Coal Briquette Delivery Campaign">
									<p><strong>Delivering Coal Briquette of Love.</strong><br />IPARK Corporate Citizenship has participated in ‘Briquette sharing campaign of warmer Korea’ since 2005. As a part of continuous Sharing Management we have delivered briquettes to low-income households, undeliverable region and single elderly households.</p>
								</div>
							</div>	

							<div class="serve">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Community</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Building Houses of Hope</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve06.jpg" alt="Building Houses of Hope">
									<p><strong>Building with a Full Heart.</strong><br />IPARK Corporate Citizenship is building houses and renovating furniture and facilities for outworn community living center (Community living facilities for handicapped) for handicapped throughout the country. By participating in ‘Renovation plan for cozy social welfare facilities,’ IPARK Corporate Citizenship is trying hard to provide cozy and pleasant living spaces for underprivileged social class.</p>
								</div>
							</div>	

							<div class="serve">
								<h2>Environment</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Nature Conservation, Green Owner</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve07.jpg" alt="Nature Conservation, Green Owner">
									<p><strong>IPARK of Love for Everyone</strong><br />IPARK Corporate Citizenship participates in green owner activity. Green owner activity is quarterly voluntary activity led by executives and staffs of construction HQ for the preservation of domestic national parks regardless of its ownership.</p>
								</div>
							</div>	

							<div class="serve">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Environment</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Volunteer Activity for Oil Cleanup at Taean.</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve08.jpg" alt="Volunteer Activity for Oil Cleanup at Taean">
									<p><strong>Sharing the Pain of Taean.</strong><br />President Chung Mong-Gyu and 50 executives and staffs of HDC and affiliates have visited Gureumpo Beach, Mohang-ri, Sowon-myeon, Taean-gun, Chungcheongnam-do to participate in oil cleanup volunteer activity. Participants have delivered their faith in overcoming the incident together by comforting residents of Taean and cleaning oils on the rocks along the beach.</p>
								</div>
							</div>	

							<div class="serve">
								<h2>Children</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Bracelet of Love</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve09.jpg" alt="Bracelet of Love">
									<p><strong>Be a Friend with Underfed Children.</strong><br />Hyundai Development Company have implemented charity bracelet campaign, BºFRIEND, with  LOVEAID Foundation. BºFRIEND engraved orange silicon bracelet means to be a friend with underfed children and the profits have been used to prepare a fund for underfed children.</p>
								</div>
							</div>	

							<div class="serve mb6">
								<h2 class="p_hidden t_hidden">Children</h2>
								<div class="hr"></div>
								<h3>Hat-knitting Campaign for Newborn Babies.</h3>
								<div class="box">
									<img src="/front/en/images/08sustainability/serve10.jpg" alt="Hat-knitting Campaign for Newborn Babies">
									<p><strong>Hat-knitting Campaign for Underdeveloped Countries’ New Born Babies.</strong><br />Hat-knitting campaign for new born babies is ran by Save the Children to help new born babies in underdeveloped countries like Bangladesh and Zambia in Africa. 35 female employees of ‘Modoori Society’ have knitted in their lunch and private time to deliver hand-knitted hats for children at underdeveloped countries with high neonatal mortality rate.</p>
								</div>
